SIMPLE: embezzle
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Embezzle
<hw>Em*bez"zle</hw> <pr>(⟦ecr⟧m*b⟦ecr⟧z"z'l)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Embezzled</conjf>
<pr>(⟦ecr⟧m*b⟦ecr⟧z"z'ld)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Embezzling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Norm. F.
<ets>embeseiller</ets> to destroy; cf. OF. <ets>besillier</ets> to ill
treat, ravage, destroy. Cf. <er>Bezzle</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
appropriate fraudulently to one's own use, as property intrusted to
one's care; to apply to one's private uses by a breach of trust; <as>as,
to <ex>embezzle</ex> money held in trust</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To misappropriate; to waste; to dissipate in
extravagance.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To <qex>embezzle</qex> our money in drinking or gaming.</q>
<rj><qau>Sharp.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>embezzled</ent>⟦br⟧
